criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. Aged 55-70 ys;
2. Diagnosed as atrophic age-related macular degeneration;
3. No CNV;
4. The BCVA of target eye will not be better than 20/400;
5. Diopter is greater than 8.00 D, axial length â‰¤28 mm;
6. Voluntary as test subjects, signed informed consent, regular follow-up will be effected according to the specified time.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. The macular atrophy  caused by other disesaes in addition to AMD;
2. With history of other eye diseases or ocular traumas;
3. With history of intraocular surgery;
4. With serious systerm diseases, ALT/AST)> 1.5 or creatine > 1.3 mg/dL;
5. With any immunodeficiency disease;
6. Subject who are receiving immunosuppressive therapy;
7. Allergic to tacrolimus or Mycophenolate mofetil;
